<DOC><DOCNO> AP880413-0021 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-13-88 0348EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Brazil-Rebellion     04-13 0169</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Brazil-Rebellion,0173</SECOND><HEAD>Brazilian Prison Rebellion Ends, Hostages Freed</HEAD><DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Six prisoners ended a rebellionand freed four hostages from a prison in northeastern Brazil.   Ricardo Leitao, spokesman for the Pernambuco state governor'soffice, said the inmates surrendered on Tuesday at the Anibal Bruniprison in Recife, the state capital, which is 1,500 miles northeastof Rio.   ``There was no problem with the surrender. The police guaranteedtheir physical safety, and they threw out their knives and thentheir guns and released the hostages,'' Leitao said in a televisedinterview from Recife.   Two priests and a nun held as hostages were released unharmed.The fourth hostage, a prison guard, had been shot in the leg whiletrying to escape.   The rebellion began Saturday during Mass at the 300-inmate,medium-security prison. The inmates took two priests, two nuns andtwo guards hostage and demanded handguns, rifles, ammunition,handcuffs, two cars and $10,000.   They later released a nun in exchange for water and one guardescaped.</TEXT></DOC>